import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['temperature'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hourly temperature in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['temperature'], data['wind'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between temperature and wind speed in Seattle in 2010?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    ax.boxplot(data['pressure'].groupby(data['hour']).mean(), vert=False, widths=0.5, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'))
    ax.set_xlabel('Average Hourly Pressure (mb)')
    ax.set_yticklabels(['12AM', '1AM', '2AM', '3AM', '4AM', '5AM', '6AM', '7AM', '8AM', '9AM', '10AM', '11AM', '12PM', '1PM', '2PM', '3PM', '4PM', '5PM', '6PM', '7PM', '8PM', '9PM', '10PM', '11PM'])
    plt.title('What is the average hourly pressure in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.grid(True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
